  <Doc::Page::Content>
    <h2 class="doc-text-h2">What is a pattern?</h2>
    <p class="doc-text-body">A pattern is a combination of components that work together to accomplish a function or
      render a layout. They are often used to solve the same problem consistently. Common examples of patterns are
      forms, navigation, button sets, etc.</p>
    <h2 class="doc-text-h2">Helios pattern support</h2>
    <p class="doc-text-body">We don't currently support patterns, but we have a few on our
      <a href="https://go.hashi.co/hds-rollout">roadmap</a>. We're also planning to introduce guidelines and best
      practices around assembling components in a consistent and scalable manner.
    </p>
    <p class="doc-text-body">If you find yourself building the same pattern often,
      <a
        href="https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLScpMXgrUTVT5fYriu4Pp48r4Nl_eCPluVnJLg0Yg3NXsRWvIA/viewform"
      >submit a new pattern request</a>.
    </p>
    <p class="doc-text-body">Don't hesitate to
      <LinkTo @route="support">contact the Design Systems Team</LinkTo>
      for best practices and suggestions when building and defining local components and patterns.
    </p>
  </Doc::Page::Content>
</Doc::Page::Stage>